<br>
My reply on other thread......<br>
<br>
IMO Trak should be taken off of a rotation, and Sev should be put on.<br>
<br>
Trak is a pain in the ass to even get to and the guilds that are on the rotation can all and do fight in ToV anyways. The reason for the Trak rotation was for VP keys, but is this really still a problem? We (VoF) killed Trak once and never have since. The reason why is because of the rotation we never were able to be up for Trak on a weekend when our forces are strong, and every weekday we were up we didn't have a good turnout. I would guess that in a month or two VoF will be capable of killing Trak any day of the week but we aren't there yet. So my question is...Should Trak be on a rotation anymore?<br>
<br>
The guilds that CAN kill him on weekdays with no problem at all can easily rush to him if he pops and kill him for his teeth. The guilds that can't necessarily kill him any day yet could go for him Fridays thru Sundays. There are probably half a dozen guilds out there that COULD kill Trak but never get the chance because they need a weekend raid to do so. I think it would benefit larger and smaller guilds to take him off rotation.<br>
<br>
Severilous is different IMO. First of all I think that as a server we should agree that if you don't have a warrior waiting for a green scale, then you don't kill Sev. Having killed Trak with my guild, I know we are more than capable of killing Sev. Of course we have never gotten the chance since he is always killed right after he spawns. Currently on the Rathe there aren't a whole lot of guilds that even have ANY warrior epics. The only reason that is the case is because the top handful of guilds are the only guilds strong enough to kill Sev quickly. There are enough guilds like this though that it won't matter when he spawns, at least one guild online at the time can kill him. These guilds that are killing Sev like this DO have warriors that need their epics, so I wouldn't fault them for killing Sev to complete the quests. Unfortunately there are MANY guilds out there that have NO warrior epics at all just because they aren't powerful enough to beat the big guilds to him.<br>
<br>
If Sev was on a rotation then those bigger guilds would STILL be able to get the warriors without epics their green scales. It would also allow the smaller guilds to get their FIRST warrior epics. Granted there are lots of guilds capable of killing Sev so the rotation might be long...but wouldn't it be fair? Let's just say there are a dozen guilds that would want on the rotation and are capable of killing Sev...with his spawntime and the extra time he would be up each time he spawned til the guild up for him kills him...I would guess each guild would get a shot every couple months. This may seem too long to wait for the bigger guilds but isn't it more fair than the way it is now? Should every smaller guild be forced to wait until the bigger guilds have every warrior with their epic until they get their first?<br>
<br>
Of course you would have the same problem with Sev as now with Trak. Guilds that CAN kill him but maybe only on a weekend. I would suggest changing the way the rotation works for this. Instead of having a guild lose its turn when they pass...why couldn't they just say they pass until the next time he is up on a weekend? This would take minimal effort in organization IMO. You would just have a list of guilds and if one passed til a weekend then just move the next guild capable of killing him on a weekday up to that guilds spot (in doing this moving the whole rotation down one slot...well...not the whole rotation just the guilds in between the one passing and the one taking over their spot).<br>
<br>
I really think something like this would be good for The Rathe as a whole and by far would be more fair than how it is now.<br>
<br>
Bogart<br>
