As Emil said a rotation on Sev would require a lot of honor in it.  I'm sure there are always people from most guilds checking on him daily, so I doubt a guild could ever kill him without everyone else finding out.  If a guild killed him that isn't on the rotation then not much could be done.<br>
<br>
I still think it might be worth considering people willing to try out a rotation always try to provide help to other guilds on it.  I think of Sev a lot like Ragefire.  The randomness of the spawn really makes it a pain.  I for one have personally seen SoT and NB (I'm sure there are many others) help other guilds with RF when it pops at a bad time.  VoF has helped others with RF before and we've also been helped.  The reason people are so helpful I think with RF is because of the grueling camp which usually involves killing gobs of FGs and people actually camping the lair for hours and hours and hours.  I wouldn't think it should be necessary to have a warrior sit in EJ until Sev spawns but wouldn't it be honorable to treat Sev the same way?  With a list of a rotation all guilds would know who was up for Sev next...that guild should then be responsible to keep a good eye out for Sev since they are up next.  If he pops at a bad time for that guild then other guilds would show a lot of class IMO to lend a helpful hand the same way they do with RF.<br>
<br>
If we just treated Sev the way we do RF and helped eachother out, then I think every guild would benefit.<br>
